<item>
            <title>[LU-9874] simplify project transfer codes</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-9874</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Currently, osd-ldiskfs call __ldiskfs_ioctl_project() to transfer project quota which is user ioctl&lt;br/&gt;
for ext4, it will start transaction and reserve credits, this is not right logic with Lustre.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Lustre have started a transaction handle and credits have been reserved during declare phase,&lt;br/&gt;
so calling __ldiskfs_ioctl_project() will cause nested handle starting, which is not a problem for jbd2&lt;br/&gt;
 because it will attach current thread&apos;s handle if transaction have been started, but in this case it will ignore credits reservation.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also Lustre don&apos;t need inode mutex protection for project transfer, Lustre have reserved enough&lt;br/&gt;
credits for project transfer, we need fix agent inode transfering.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
